entries.name: PredicatePermitter
entries.description: Contract that connects INTMAX deposits to the Predicate AVS that ultimately checks AML requirements. It stores a policy ID to be then referenced by the Predicate AVS.

receivedPermissions.description: can add and remove permissioned operators, deregister regular operators, register new policies, override existing policies, and in general manage the AVS (e.g. thresholds, strategies) and the connection to EigenLayer.

entries.name: Contribution
entries.description: Records a set of 'contribution' actions by saving addresses with a tag of their action (e.g. propose blocks, claim withdrawals, deposit...).

receivedPermissions.description: can relay deposits to the main rollup contract on Scroll.

entries.name: Liquidity
entries.description: Entry point of the project. Handles deposits, withdrawals, and the communication from and to the main rollup contract on Scroll. Deposits are gated by an AML check.
